    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nLatest master\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 12\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom source\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nPut this into `mwe.lua`:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal function feed_keys(s)\r\n  vim.api.nvim_feedkeys(vim.api.nvim_replace_termcodes(s, true, true, true), 'n', false)\r\nend\r\n\r\nlocal function working()\r\n  assert(vim.fn.mode() == 'i')\r\n  feed_keys('foo<C-g>ubar')\r\nend\r\n\r\nlocal function insert_text_at_cursor(text)\r\n  local line = vim.fn.line('.') - 1\r\n  local col = vim.fn.col('.') - 1\r\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_text(0, line, col, line, col, {text})\r\nend\r\n\r\nlocal function broken()\r\n  assert(vim.fn.mode() == 'i')\r\n  insert_text_at_cursor('foo')\r\n  feed_keys('<C-g>u')\r\n  insert_text_at_cursor('bar')\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set('i', '<C-a>', working)\r\nvim.keymap.set('i', '<C-b>', broken)\r\n```\r\n\r\n- `nvim --clean`\r\n- `:source mwe.lua`\r\n- `i<C-a><Esc>`\r\n- `u` ‚Üí deletes \"bar\" ‚úÖ\r\n- `u` ‚Üí deletes \"foo\" ‚úÖ\r\n- `i<C-b><Esc>`\r\n- `u` ‚Üí deletes \"foobar\" ‚ùå\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`<C-g>u` breaks the undo sequence, including for buffer edits made via API functions.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`<C-g>u` is unaware that a change to the buffer has happened after `nvim_buf_set_text`.",
