        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "For posterity, this seems to work:\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_feedkeys(\n-- create new \"undo\" point\n  vim.api.nvim_replace_termcodes('<C-g>u', true, true, true),\n  'n', false)\n-- then continue with whatever is next, even tho it is technically not synchronous:\ncmp.confirm()\n```\nbut this might be the guaranteed synchronous code:\n```lua\n-- create new \"undo\" point\nvim.cmd(\"let &undolevels = &undolevels\") -- to hide stock statusline\ncmp.confirm()\n```",
